    "content": "CONSENSUS: APPROVED\n\nProduct review of Step 9 design:\n\n- Scope is exactly right: one clarify path (inbox -> waiting for), matching the established patterns from Steps 5 and 7.\n- Using the inbox item's existing title for the WaitingForItem is correct — no reason to make the user re-type it. The only new field needed is waiting_on, which is the distinguishing information for this list.\n- Progressive disclosure (radio button reveals waiting_on field, hides context selector) follows the same UX pattern users already know from clarify-as-next-action and clarify-as-project.\n- Deferred items are explicitly out of scope. Good.\n\nNo blocking feedback. Ready to implement."
